Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees.

Open package of @chopped chicken breast{10%ounce} and drain off any excess liquid. In #oven-ready tray{}, combine chicken, @orzo pasta{4%ounce}, @cannellini beans{1} and their liquid, @chicken stock concentrate{2}, @dried oregano{1%teaspoon}, @garlic powder{1%teaspoon}, @cream cheese{2%tablespoon}, and 1/4 cup water (for 4 servings, divide between two trays, using 1/4 cup water for each tray). Drizzle mixture with @olive oil{}.

Cover chicken orzo bake with #foil{} and bake on top rack until chicken is fully cooked and bake is bubbling, ~{30-35%minutes} (for 4 servings, place two trays side by side on top rack).

Meanwhile, crush @pistachios{1/2%ounce} in their package. In a #small bowl{}, combine @green goddess dressing{2%ounce}, 1 tablespoon olive oil, and 1 tablespoon water (2 tablespoon olive oil and 2 tablespoon water for 4 servings). Taste and season with a pinch of @salt{}.

Carefully remove foil from chicken orzo bake (watch out for steam!); stir. Taste and season with salt and @pepper{}.

Top with @feta cheese{1/2%cup} and crushed pistachios. Drizzle with green goddess sauce. Divide between plates or #shallow bowls{}; serve with @chili flakes{1%teaspoon} on the side.

> Poultry is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.